<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&message.id=3855#M3855">126</a> of 159
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 675 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P>Such great ideas!</P>
<P>Well I have some ideas for some new spells and sorry if they have been mentioned before since I started reading this thread and managed to get half way through all the posts after an hour and realised I would run out of time to post my own thoughts before I have to leave for Portugal <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></P>
<P>I'd like to see a spell called <STRONG><FONT color=#ffff66 size=4>Transpose</FONT></STRONG> which will swap any targeted group member with the wizard casting the spell in the same zone. This will make the labourious duty of being the twin in the coh summon team much easier. Make it a 10+ sec cast to avoid exploits on agro if necessary although most mobs now summon etc.</P>
<P>Second spell I'd like to see for int casters is <STRONG><FONT color=#ffff66 size=4>Kinectic shield</FONT></STRONG>. This spell severely mitigates any physical ranged attacks. Wizards need this desparately to stand a chance in pvp vs auto targeting melee range classes that hit for 2k a pop. Could also be used in a stratagy based trial when casters might be needed to dodge a gauntlet of ranged missile traps etc.</P>
<P>Third spell I'd like to see is an upgrade to harvest - about time even if us high end casters dont really need it.</P>
<P>My fourth spell that needs an upgrade is concussion. Ancient concussion should be researchable as mentioned already but more importantly a new item with clicky ancient concussion or new agro reducing spell should be brought into the game as we have come a long way from when concussion came out and was useful compared to the nukes we now have - 5k base 1550 mana Etherfire. Currently there is only the ele pants which are really out of their league in tacvi, anguish and dreadsphire statwise by 150 pct. </P>
<P>Mind crash should get some hastening aa's in the new expansion if no new concussion spells are due.</P>
<P>Manaburn is a bit of a joke amongst wizards that paid for it versus those who didnt :/ It needs to be thought over since the one min stacking issue was meant to prevent inbalance but the crit remains at 9472 or about. Wizzies in my guild crit for 16k plus with focus's and ACF. Will probably crit for 20k now with Etherfire and can cast this many times together before a summon which clearly makes manaburn look daft. Manaburn should of been a insta cast to make it anything worthwhile in its current form. </P>
<P>Translocate to eye or to scounting familiar sounds like a brilliant new addition and will make up for the lack of content re our new spells over the last seven expansions give or take a few here and there. Be nice to get an eye that can swim under water too and/or levitate I.E <FONT color=#ffff66 size=4><STRONG>Eye of Coirnav </STRONG></FONT>for swimming and <FONT color=#ffff66 size=4><STRONG>Eye of Xegony </STRONG></FONT>for levitate.</P>
<P>Peace</P>
<P>Fortunbas Soulsender</P>
<P>7th degree Sorceror</P>
<P>Antonius Bayle</P>
<P>Proud member of Darkwind</P>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>08-26-2005</span> <span class=time_text>06:23 AM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
