<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&message.id=3862#M3862">128</a> of 159
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 642 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>A few ideas, posted them on Graffe's too, but thought I'd throw them here in the official forum as well.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>A magic missile like spell line that acted as a ranged weapon type attack.&nbsp; For example you basically are casting a small burst of magic on autofire/autoattack that doesn't rely on the spell timer.&nbsp; The spell (summons an item that?) acts like a 10/25 ranged weapon at say level 50 (adjust accordingly to current level).&nbsp; It would act like a ranged weapon with chances to miss (although I'd suggest a heavy attack bonus to this).&nbsp; This fills the gap between casts and allows a mana free alternative to allow you to contribute damage to a fight.&nbsp; Alternatively make it an AA with a hotkey and a 2-3 second refresh timer.&nbsp; Basically lets you click off a 100-200+ point mana free shot every 2-3 seconds independent of the spell timer.&nbsp; Follow the progression line and you can start releasing multiple bolts at a shot (Double attack?&nbsp; Triple attack?&nbsp; The ability to shoot bolts from both hands?).&nbsp;&nbsp; This is classic fantasy RPG caster fodder, the ability for powerful wizards to summon minor magic to deal with small foes or to fill the time between really impressive displays of magic.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>BTW there is nothing that keeps this alternate idea from being made into a spell.&nbsp; Spell refresh times are something that can in fact be adjusted.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Short (melee) range, low mana, HIGH damage touch type spells.&nbsp; I.E. you can do extremely high damage in exchange for giving up your range advantage.&nbsp; Instead of channeling the energy into a manifestation that has to bridge the gap between yourself and the target, you release the magic directly into the target.&nbsp; This should be extremely popular with developers since it solves the problem with how to increase our damage without making kiting even more attractive.&nbsp; Example would be 6000 damage, 600 mana, 25 range, 2.0 sec cast time.</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>08-26-2005</span> <span class=time_text>09:23 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_rating_cell" valign=bottom nowrap 
			
			>
			
				&nbsp;
				
