<img src="/eq/i/icons/Classes/wizard.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&message.id=4336#M4336">145</a> of 159
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 293 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN class=""></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P><SPAN>I think one of the main reasons people start a wizard are the image given from good fantasy books.&nbsp; (Gandalf being a prime example.)&nbsp; Everyone knows that Gandalf has supreme power through the books.&nbsp; I would like to be known for our power in the game as well.<BR>&nbsp;<BR>We started out as the porting masters; I think we should get the title back.&nbsp; Reverse CotH is a great idea, as well as the other port ideas.&nbsp; I also agree with the shadowstep in a direction spell.&nbsp; Perhaps a high cast time line of sight port spell.&nbsp; The cast time would make it undesirable to use in battle, but would give us a version of SOW that works well. <BR>&nbsp;<BR>I also would like to be able to summon mobs to me.&nbsp; Some mobs still run really fast when low on life, as a wizard, why can't I scream, "You shall not evade me, stupid pixie" and call them back to me.&nbsp; The mobs can do it, why can't I?<BR>&nbsp;<BR>Another spell I would like to see, perhaps just for fun or adventure, would be a random port spell.&nbsp; I remember back in the pre-eq days I used to play MUDs.&nbsp; One of the fun pastimes was to put all your equip in the bank and get every buff you could and start porting.&nbsp; The reason being is there were some rooms in the game (gods chambers, etc) that were inaccessible by any other means.&nbsp; Of course, there is always the chance of porting to your instant death, but that was half the adventure.&nbsp; It was also a good way to see new areas.&nbsp; This could also be used to get some rare equipment that can only be achieved by spending hours porting and praying to land in a port only room.<BR>&nbsp;<BR>I also would like to see a fix for our resists...&nbsp; At level 30, I can group with people my own level and take on red mobs in EC.&nbsp; Just because they are red to us doesn't mean a good group can't kill them.&nbsp; However, being the wizard, I rely on my spells to contribute to the group.&nbsp; I've gone through all of my mana with every spell being resisted.&nbsp; Doesn't seem right that other members of the group can still kill the mob when I can't even contribute one point of damage due to resists.&nbsp; (Magic, Fire, Ice, Lightening.. nothing works... *sighs*)<BR>&nbsp;<BR>There should also be a line of spells for pure roleplay.&nbsp; While some may love only the attack, I like to actually play a wizard.&nbsp; I would love to have a damage shield or something that covers me in flickering lightening.&nbsp; I'd love to at least appear an awesome wizard.&nbsp; If you can make it to a high level, you deserve at least that much.<BR>&nbsp;<BR>&nbsp;I would love to have my pet be able to speak and fetch stuff for me.&nbsp; I know he's just a familiar, but in every fantasy setting with familiar, the wizard was able to use the familiar for scrying or speaking.&nbsp; I would like to see some use for them other than to make flappy noises.<BR>&nbsp;<BR>Another thing... give us a way to protect ourself when OOM.&nbsp; If we don’t' have clarity, even a green mob can kill us if we run out of mana at the wrong point.&nbsp; Bashing keeps us from running, and we have almost no skill at any martial combat.&nbsp; Even a low damage no mana magic missile would be welcome to kill off annoying skeletons and whatever decides to attack us while medding.&nbsp; Make this a class skill that doesn't use a spell slot.&nbsp; It might do no good at high levels (since you'd use down time on a raid to med rather than doing 50 points damage every few seconds) but it would help take away some minor annoyances with the class.<BR>&nbsp;<BR>&nbsp;<BR>Also, while not really only to wizards, I would really like to see languages have a point in the game.&nbsp; When I think of how a well known wizard (ie: Gandalf once again) and how he became so powerful, I know he had to study for a long time.&nbsp; Even in the books you see him researching about the ring.&nbsp; He reads the language of the dark one.&nbsp; He reads all kinds of manuals in different languages.&nbsp; He has to do all this stuff to figure out what’s happening.&nbsp; Why don't the language skills matter in our research?&nbsp; You'd think if you learning a spell created by a Old elf that you would have to know Elder Elvish to learn the spell.&nbsp; I truly think that along with our research skill, our languages should come into the picture when figuring out if your research combine was successful.&nbsp; I know a lot of people would complain at having to do one more thing, but I honestly don't know why this isn't already a requirement.&nbsp; It only makes sense in my mind.&nbsp; Also, some quests shouldn't be completeable unless you can hail and talk to that old dragon in Elder Dragon.&nbsp; No old dragon I know would bestow his secrets to any normal human, and speaking in their language would certainly get their attention.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Please make languages have some point in the game other than for a little charm!<BR>&nbsp;<BR>It is a game, and I do enjoy playing it, but sometimes I think they took out aspects of the game to make it easier for people.&nbsp; I don't think things should be easy (everyone speaking common) but I do think it should be fun.&nbsp; I do think all classes should get things that do nothing for the game other than to allow them to be that character.&nbsp;&nbsp; Role playing is good.<BR>&nbsp;<BR>My two cents... Hope it means something.</SPAN></P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							-- <br>Grongel - 70 Wizard of Ro<br>Utaboshi Starsong - 58 Bard of None<br>Bonds of Honor<br>Stromm Server<br><br>"I'm not kiting!  I'm just waiting for the tank to catch up."
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
